
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `apg` (Automated Password Generator) baraye dorost kardane password-haye ghavi va tasadofi (random) estefade mishavad.  In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta password-haye amni dorost konid ke haminjoori hads zadan anha sakht bashad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `apg -n 10`  --> 🔢 Dorost kardane 10 ta password
    🔹 `apg -m 16`  --> 🔒 Password-haye 16 character-i dorost mikonad
    🔹 `apg -a 0`   --> 🚫 Password-ha faghat shamel character haye alfanumeric mishavand(bedune symbole digar)

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ apg

    🔹 Dorost kardane yek password tasadofi ba etela'ate pishfarz

    $ apg -n 5 -m 12

    🔹 Dorost kardane 5 ta password ba drazaye 12 character

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ apg -n 3 -m 8 -a 0

    🔹 In dastoor 3 ta password-e 8 character-i dorost mikonad ke faghat az horoof va adad tashkil shode ast, bedune hich symbole digar.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `apg` (Automated Password Generator) command is used to generate strong, random passwords. It helps you create secure passwords that are difficult to guess.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `apg -n 10`  --> 🔢 Generate 10 passwords
    🔹 `apg -m 16`  --> 🔒 Generate 16-character passwords
    🔹 `apg -a 0`   --> 🚫 Passwords will only contain alphanumeric characters (no other symbols)

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ apg

    🔹 Generate a single random password using default settings.

    $ apg -n 5 -m 12

    🔹 Generate 5 passwords with a length of 12 characters.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ apg -n 3 -m 8 -a 0

    🔹 This command generates 3 passwords, each 8 characters long, using only alphanumeric characters (no symbols).
